redshifts very similar to that of the actual ones and thus allow us to\nuse pseudo-redshifts for our statistical study. We use the reduced chi-square\nand the maximization of the log-likelihood to statistically analyze the\ndistribution of Fermi GRB durations. Both methods show that the distribution of\nthe observed and the intrinsic bursts durations are better represented by two\ngroups, rather than three.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Oct 2018 16:50:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-10"}
